{"version":"1.2","person":{"datePublished":"2023-12-27","name":"Gwynnog Farfsych ap Lles","nameForms":[{"lang":"en","fullText":"Gwynnog Farfsych ap Lles","parts":[{"type":"http://gedcomx.org/Given","value":"Gwynnog Farfsych ap"},{"type":"http://gedcomx.org/Surname","value":"Lles"}],"order":"EUROTYPIC"}],"gender":"Male","lifespan":"0870–Male","fullLifespan":"about 870–","memoryArtifacts":[{"memoryType":"PHOTO","url":"https://sg30p0.familysearch.org/service/records/storage/dascloud/patron/v2/TH-7710-114981-17840-15/dist.jpg?ctx=ArtCtxPublic","memoryUrl":"https://www.familysearch.org/photos/artifacts/143176496","thumbnailUrl":"https://sg30p0.familysearch.org/service/records/storage/dascloud/patron/v2/TH-7710-114981-17840-15/thumb200s.jpg?ctx=ArtCtxPublic","deepZoomUrl":"https://sg30p0.familysearch.org/service/records/storage/deepzoomcloud/dzpatron/v1/TH-7710-114981-17840-15/scale?ctx=ArtCtxPublic","@type":"ImageObject"}],"birthDate":"+0870","birthPlace":{"address":"Wales","geo":{"latitude":52.33022,"longitude":-3.76641,"@type":"GeoCoordinates"},"@type":"Place"},"deathPlace":{"address":"Montgomeryshire, Wales, United Kingdom","geo":{"latitude":52.5628,"longitude":-3.1493,"@type":"GeoCoordinates"},"@type":"Place"},"userCertifiedLifeSummary":"He is identified by Boyer [1] in the pedigree of Gwaithfoed of Powys: Gwaithfoed ap Gwynnan ap Gwynnog Farefsych ap Lles Llawddeog ap Ceidio ap Corf ap Caenog ap Tegonwy ap Teon ap Gwineu Deufreuddwyd ap Brwyr Lew ap Bwydeg ap Rhun Rhudd Baladr ap Llary ap Casnar Wledig as one of Gwaithfoed of Powy's ancestors. Boyer does not provide individual descriptions of each generation, as only the name is given and it is likely that some or many are legendary. Boyer notes that the first eight generations of this pediree are the same as for the line of Trahaearn ap Caradog, with one generation difference. Gwaithfoed's pedigree appears in ahnentafel form at Legendary Ancestors of Gwaithfoed of Powys.\n\nThe National Library of Wales writes that the correct pedigree for Gwaithfoed of Powys, based on MG3 with corrections from later versions, seems to have been Gaithfoed ap Gwynnan ap Gwynnog Farfsych ap Lies llawddeog ap Ceidio ap Corf ap Caenog ap Tegonwy. \" [2] This is consistent with Boyer's presentation.\n\nPedigree\nAfter analysis, Darrell Wolcott [3] has presented the following table of Lies Llyddog's descendants:\n\nLies Llyddog, born say 855\nGwynnog Farfsych, born, say 885\nGwaithfoed of Powys, born, say, 915\nGwerystan, born, say, 950\nCynfyn, born, say, 985\nBleddyn, born, say, 1025\nCaradog, born say, 890\nGwrydr Hir, born, say, 920\nGwaithfoed of Tegeingl, born, say, 955\nNeiniad, born, say, 985\nEdnowain Bendew, born, say, 1020\nSources\n↑ Carl Boyer 3rd. Medieval Welsh Ancestors of Certain Americans. Generally follows Bartrum. By the author: Santa Clarita, California, 2004. Gwaithfoed and his ancestors are #1-15 on page 9.\n↑ National Library of Wales Journal National Library of Wales journal - Cyf. 13, rh. 2 Gaeaf 1963 Pedigrees of the Welsh tribal Patriarchs. The National Library of Wales has created and published this digital version of the journal under a licence granted by the publisher. The material it contains may be used for all purposes while respecting the moral rights of the creators. Accessed August 18, 2018 jhd\n↑ Darrell Wolcott. Ancient Wales Studies Sorting out the Gwaithfoeds Accessed 24 July 2022. jhd","events":[{"name":"Birth","sources":"0","year":"0870","date":"about 870","place":"Wales"},{"name":"Marriage","sources":"0","year":"0890","date":"before 890","place":"Montgomeryshire, Wales","type":"Spousal","age":"19","id":"GWSC-CVL"},{"name":"Birth of Child","sources":"0","year":"0890","date":"about 0890","place":"Powys, Wales","age":"20","id":"G25C-9YL"},{"name":"Birth of Child","sources":"0","year":"0890","date":"Abt 890","place":"Powys, Cymru","age":"20","id":"GGW9-K2T"},{"name":"Death","sources":"0","place":"Montgomeryshire, Wales, United Kingdom"},{"name":"Marriage","so